i have heard that goats milk is good for you does anyone know if this is true goat milk has more easily digestible fat and protein content than cow milk the increased digestibility of protein is of importance to infant diets both human and animal as well as to invalid and convalescent diets goat milk tends to have a better buffering quality which is good for the treatment of ulcers in under developed countries where meat consumption is low goat milk is an important daily food source of protein phosphate and calcium not available otherwise because of a lack of cow milk goat milk can successfully replace cow milk in diets of those who are allergic to cow milk the value of goat milk as an alternative food for children and sick people because it is easier digested extends also to feeding animals young dogs foals even calves Milk Breast milk Dairy Livestock Veganism Insulin Protein Soy milk Breastfeeding Soybean Cheese Infant formula Vegetarianism Goat Food Nutrition Bovine spongiform encephalopathy Vitamin C Domestic goat Crohn's disease Diarrhea Neolithic Revolution Food allergy Cat Ulcerative colitis Kashrut Dieting Guinea pig Dairy cattle Coeliac disease Omega-3 fatty acid Factory farming Soy protein Elephant Kosher foods Atkins Nutritional Approach Domestic rabbit Sewage treatment Whale Chicken Protein-energy malnutrition Yoghurt Sugar Chocolate Beef Hamster Vitamin D Growth hormone treatment Organic food Low-carbohydrate diet Dairy farming Vegetarian nutrition Dietary fiber Foot-and-mouth disease Bovine somatotropin Brain Gastroesophageal reflux disease Hypoglycemia Environmental vegetarianism Horse Healthy eating Folic acid Slaughterhouse Dog Hypomagnesemia Gelatin Peanut Neolithic Ferret Kitten Jewish cuisine Egg (food) Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Raw food diet Trans fat Acne Sacred cow Domestication Carnivorous plant Cancer Fancy rat Kidney stone Pasteurization Saturated fat Glycemic index Teat Bodybuilding Anemia Soft drink Calcium in biology 